description: From Latin extructus, exstructus, past participle of extruere, exstruere (“to build up”), from ex (“out”) + struere (“to build”).

verbs.description: extruct (third-person singular simple present extructs, present participle extructing, simple past and past participle extructed)

examples: These high extructed Spires he writ / That mortal Deltius must quit.
